div.p:
describes the direction in which the arpeggio is to be performed;
            "nonarp" indicates a non-arpeggiated chord, usually rendered with a
            preceding bracket instead of a wavy line.

records the vertical adjustment of the entity's
            programmatically-determined location in terms of interline distance;
            that is, units of 1/2 the distance between adjacent staves.
